{"questionId":"5622","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Enthalpy changes depend on the number and type of bonds broken and formed.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The table lists the standard enthalpies of formation, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\Delta H_{\\text{f}}^\\Theta \">\n  <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n  <msubsup>\n    <mi>H</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>f</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Θ</mi>\n  </msubsup>\n</math></span>, for some of the species in the&nbsp;reaction above.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4612/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-10_om_08.21.04.png\" alt=\"M18/4/CHEMI/SP2/ENG/TZ2/04.b\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Outline why no value is listed for H<sub>2</sub>(g).</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\Delta H_{\\text{f}}^\\Theta \">\n  <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n  <msubsup>\n    <mi>H</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>f</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Θ</mi>\n  </msubsup>\n</math></span> for any element =&nbsp;0 <strong>«</strong>by definition<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p>no energy required to form an element <strong>«</strong>in its stable form<strong>» </strong>from itself</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"5622","referenceCode":"18M.2.sl.TZ2.4b.i","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Outline why no value is listed for H2(g).","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Energetics/thermochemistry","5.2 Hess’s Law","Core","Topic 5: Energetics/thermochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}